<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1263,1650]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,1343,1369]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
The taxonomy and intraspecific morphological variations of this species are discussed in depth by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig" box="[188,330,1384,1410]" pageId="22" pageNumber="46" refString="Haig, J. (1964) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 1916. 81. Porcellanid crabs from the Indo- West Pacific, Part I. Videnskabelige Meddelelser Dansk Naturhistrisk Forening i Kj g benhavn, 126, 355 - 386." type="journal article" year="1964">
Haig (
<number box="[260,321,1384,1410]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nakasone" box="[387,719,1384,1410]" pageId="22" pageNumber="48" refString="Nakasone, Y. &amp; Miyake, S. (1971) Porcellanid crabs (Anomura: Porcellanidae) from New Caledonia and the Fiji Islands. Biological Magazine of Okinawa, 8, 1 - 13, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1971">
Nakasone &amp; Miyake (
<number box="[647,710,1384,1410]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The variations have been known for the length-breadth ratio of the carpus of the cheliped and development of the dorsoflexor teeth, development of a tuft of plumose setae in the gape of the fingers of cheliped, and armature on the extensor margins of the meri of the amburatory legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
